text=(:if [ authgroup @tas || authgroup @admins || equal {$Author} '' ]:)%0a%0a(:toggle id=gi show="show grading interface" hide="hide grading interface":)%0a%0a>>id=gi%3c%3c%0a%0a[[GradebookArticles.{$Name}|See article in gradebook]] \\%0a[[{$FullName}?action=diff|See all changes to article]] \\%0a[[{$FullName}?action=edit|Edit this page]] \\%0aStatus: {GradebookArticles.{$Name}$:Status} %0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%0a>>%3c%3c%0a%0a----%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a[[!{$:Category}]]%0a%0a!Peruvian Sign Language (PSL) Education%0a%0a:Author: tiagocecchi1216%0a%0a'''Summary:''' \\%0a%0a[[#summary]]%0a%0aThe Peruvian government's attempts at improving the education for the deaf and the hard of hearing backfires.%0a%0a[[#summaryends]]%0a%0a----%0a[[#content]]%0a%0aPeruvian Sign Language (PSL) is a Peruvian language primarily used by the deaf in Peru. It has about 10,000 speakers, despite there being about 500,000 people in Peru with hearing disabilities.%0a%0a%0aSince 2010, the Peruvian government has implemented an "inclusive" education system for deaf students. This consists of placing deaf students in general public education classrooms, with students that don't have similar disabilities. This stands in contrast with previous attempts at educating the deaf, which usually consisted of private special education schools whose classrooms consisted entirely of the deaf or similarly disabled. %0a%0a%0aDespite this policy being an attempt at helping people with hearing disabilities, in practice it has not had success and has actually resulted in a more unequal education for those students who are deaf or have other hearing disabilities. Public school are underfunded, and in particular the teachers are not trained to deal with deaf students. This is particularly true outside of Lima, Peru's capital. As a result, the experience of the deaf students in the class is vastly different to the other students. These deaf students are isolated and simply do not learn at the rate of the other students.%0a%0a%0aSince these children are not taught PSL in school, they have now developed their own rudimentary methods of communication between each other. They now have difficulty communicating with the older deaf people. Older generations of deaf people, educated through the old special education system, are fluent in PSL, and thus have formed strong PSL-speaking communities. This disconnect from the deaf community further compounds the poor education these youth receive in school and the general isolation from the rest of society. However, t should also be noted that the special education system itself also left deaf adults with poor literacy and mathematics skills, making it difficult for them to hold down jobs.%0a%0a%0aAttempts by the government to adress the problems with inclusive education have been equally disastrous. Special LSP seminars for teachers have low attendance and generally have ineffective pedagogy. It does not seem that any genuine change in this education system is coming from the side of the Peruvian government any time soon.%0a%0a[[#contentends]]%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Expansions:%0a[[#expansions]]%0a%0a[[#expansionsend]]%0a%0a----%0a%25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%0a(:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%0a(:elseif [ equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:andrewid} '' || equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:section} '' ] :)%0a%0aYou must enter your andrew ID and section before submitting an expansion. %0a%0a(:else:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Comments%0a%0a%0a%0a%0a----%0a(:if equal {$Author} {$:Author}:)%0a!!Change article category%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#changearticlecategory:)%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a%0a(:Section: A:)%0a(:Category: SignLanguage:)%0a(:Title: Peruvian Sign Language (PSL) Education:)
